<task id="041" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Frontend — Create six TypeScript interfaces for three-pane coordination data contracts</title>
    <phase>Phase 4: Frontend — SpaarkeAi Compose Surface</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <tags>frontend, react, typescript, fluent-ui, forms, validation</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Task tags include 'fluent-ui' (UI implementation per ADR-021)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>F</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>New file in `types/` directory — no edit overlap with 040 or 044.</parallel-reason>
    <dependencies>002</dependencies>
    <blocks>042,043,045,046</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the six TypeScript interfaces that codify the three-pane coordination data contracts surfaced by Spike #2 (Workspace ↔ Context ↔ Assistant). These are the locked design.md §5 interfaces. Receivers can be stubs in R1 — the contract IS the deliverable per CLAUDE.md (Implementation Notes). Per FR-20, all six must compile and be wired (receivers stubbed); the smoke test (Phase 6) confirms data flow.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript developer fluent in cross-pane event-bus contracts (PaneEventBus pattern), Fluent UI v9 idioms, and the SpaarkeAi component model.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Six interfaces compile cleanly under `strict` mode; exported from `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/compose-contracts.ts`; consumed by Tasks 042/045 receivers (stubbed). Build green; ui-test green; dark mode N/A (type-only file but smoke harness must render).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-20 + design.md §5 + spec.md Affected Areas Frontend lock the six data contracts from Spike #2. CLAUDE.md Implementation Notes mandate that the contracts ship FIRST; receivers can be stubs. This task delivers the contract surface.
    </background>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Any rendering surface used to validate (smoke harness) MUST honor Fluent v9 dark mode.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">If contracts include any auth-scoped fields, MUST reference `@spaarke/auth` types — do NOT redefine.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">REUSE existing types directory conventions; NO new abstraction layer.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Interfaces MUST match the locked Spike #2 artifact in `notes/spikes/spike-three-pane-wiring.md` byte-for-byte (or supersede it with a documented amendment).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>`src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/` is the canonical types directory (verified via Glob). Existing files (e.g., shell types, conversation types) do NOT cover Workspace↔Context↔Assistant cross-pane flows for Compose.</existing>
    <extension>No — six new interfaces are needed because Compose introduces three-pane coordination flows not present in any existing surface. Cannot extend existing types without conflating concerns.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-20 fails — TypeScript compilation cannot verify cross-pane data contracts; Tasks 042/043/045 ship with `any` types and silent runtime drift; smoke test (Phase 6) cannot assert payload shape.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/plan.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/BUILD-A-NEW-WORKSPACE-WIDGET.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/LEGALWORKSPACE-EMBEDDED-MODE-CONTRACT.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/utils/launch-resolver.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/shell/ThreePaneShell.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/CalendarWorkspaceWidget</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">Verify context &lt; 70%. Load design.md §5, spec.md FR-20, and the Spike #2 artifact in `notes/spikes/`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Inventory existing types">Glob `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/*.ts`; confirm none cover the six Compose flows. Match the file-naming + export-style of neighbors.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Author six interfaces">Create `compose-contracts.ts` with the six locked interfaces (exact names per Spike #2 artifact). Add JSDoc citing FR-20 + design.md §5 for each.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Stub receivers minimally">In `compose-contracts.ts`, export a `ComposeEventBusContract` type union so PaneEventBus can validate dispatch shapes. Receivers themselves stay in Tasks 042/043/045.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Build TypeScript">Run `npm run build` in SpaarkeAi; confirm zero errors under `strict`.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Run shared client build">Run `pwsh ./scripts/Build-AllClientComponents.ps1`.</step>
    <step order="6" name="UI test execution">Run the ui-tests defined below — the smoke harness validates type imports + a minimal render.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 041 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Component Renders">A minimal harness component that imports all six types and renders an empty Fluent v9 `Surface` — no console errors.</test>
    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">Harness surface renders in dark theme using semantic tokens — no hard-coded hex.</test>
    <test name="Contract Shape Validation">Compile-time assertion: each of the six interfaces is exported, has expected required fields per Spike #2, and the discriminated union `ComposeEventBusContract` covers all six.</test>
  </ui-tests>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build TypeScript (strict)</tool>
    <tool name="pwsh">Run Build-AllClientComponents.ps1</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/types/compose-contracts.ts</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All six interfaces exported from `compose-contracts.ts`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` succeeds with no TS errors under `strict`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ui-tests green: Component Renders, Dark Mode Compliance, Contract Shape Validation.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Interfaces match Spike #2 artifact in `notes/spikes/spike-three-pane-wiring.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md status for task 041 is ✅.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
